Laporan Terintegrasi 2023 • P T Samator Indo Gas Tbk

Internal control is a process designed and implemented by  the  Board  of  Commissioners,  the  Board  of  Directors, and  other  members  of  management,  as  well  as  all Company  personnel,  to  provide  adequate  assurance  in achieving effective and efficient operations, reliable and accurate financial reporting, compliance with applicable laws and regulations, and the implementation of a check and balance mechanism.

The  Board  of  Directors  is  responsible  for  ensuring  the implementation of the Company's internal control system  as  part  of  GCG  implementation.  The  Company's internal  control  system  also  underlines  the  principles of transparency, law-abiding, and environmental responsibility.

In general, the Company's Internal Control System includes the following:

- 1. Structured and disciplined internal control environment;
- 2. Risk  identification  and  assessment  related  to  the Company's various business activities;
- 3. Relevant information systems, quality of information generated,  and  individual  communications  in  their roles and responsibilities concerning internal control;
- 4. Control activities are always carried out by stipulating the policies and procedures of management;
- 5. Monitoring  and  corrective  actions  on  any  arising infringements.

The Company's internal control system is elaborated in its business  conduct  guidelines  and  reference  documents, such  as  Quality  Manual  (QM),  Quality  System  Procedure (QSP), Standard Operating Procedure (SOP), and Working Instruction  (WI)  regarding  all  production  activities  and other  supporting  activities  which  will  be  continuously improved.

## Compliance with the 2013 COSO Internal Control Framework

The  Company's  internal  control  system  principles  and aspects comply with the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (COSO) framework, which divides the definition of internal control  into  5  (five)  interrelated  components,  namely control  environment,  risk  assessment,  control  activities, information and communication, and monitoring.

## Kode Etik Perseroan

## Code of Conduct

Kode Etik Perseroan merupakan sebuah pedoman dalam berperilaku dan  berbisnis yang  mengadopsi  prinsipprinsip moral yang berlaku secara umum, sebagai panduan bagi  seluruh  Insan  Perseroan  dalam  menjalankan  tugas dan  tanggung  jawabnya.  Setiap  tindakan  pelanggaran terhadap  kode  etik  perilaku  dan  bisnis  akan  diberikan sanksi sesuai ketentuan.

Kode Etik memuat pernyataan tertulis tentang nilai-nilai etika yang berlaku di lingkungan Perseroan. Versi terbaru Kode  Etik  Perseroan  telah  disahkan  pada  17  April  2023, dan berlaku secara efektif untuk menjadi standar perilaku yang  diwajibkan  bagi  seluruh  Insan  Perseroan.  Setiap individu wajib mematuhi  Kode  Etik  Perseroan  tanpa terkecuali.  Jika  terdapat  indikasi  penyimpangan,  maka Kode Etik Perseroan menjadi acuan untuk menyikapi serta memutuskan penanganan penyimpangan tersebut.

## Pokok-Pokok Kode Etik

Kode  Etik  Perseroan  mengatur  aspek-aspek  etika  yang menjadi standar perilaku untuk ditaati oleh seluruh Insan Perseroan.  Pedoman  Perilaku  mencakup  hal-hal  berikut ini:

- 1. Visi, misi, dan nilai Perseroan;
- 2. Etika bisnis Perseroan;
- 3. Kewajiban mematuhi dan hukuman pelanggaran Kode Etik;
- 4. Etika bekerja dengan pelanggan dan pemasok;
- 5. Standar etika karyawan;
- 6. Keluh kesah karyawan;
- 7. Pengungkap kecurangan; dan
- 8. Tanggung jawab sosial.

## Sosialisasi Kode Etik

Kode Etik Perseroan disosialisasikan kepada semua insan Perseroan melalui berbagai media, seperti:

- 1. Situs Web Perseroan;
- 2. Laporan Tahunan; dan
- 3. Platform internal karyawan yaitu mysamator.com.

Perseroan menegakkan Kode Etik dengan beberapa cara, di antaranya:

- 1. Setiap  karyawan  diharuskan  menandatangani  Kode Etik saat bergabung dengan Perseroan;
- 2. Sosialisasi  regular  melalui  platform  karyawan  dan Lingkar Pagi yang diadakan setiap pagi sebelum jam kerja dimulai.

