## Upaya Pengendalian Emisi

Adapun  upaya  Perseroan  dalam  mengendalikan  emisi adalah sebagai berikut:

- · Pada pabrik-pabrik yang memiliki lahan luas, Perseroan menerapkan konsep green factory untuk menghijaukan lahan  yang  tidak  terbangun  dengan  tanaman  untuk mengurangi  polusi  udara  dan  menciptakan  suasana pabrik yang makin rindang dan asri;
- · Menggunakan teknologi pemisahan, penangkapan dan  pemanfaatan  (Carbon  Capture  and  Utilization technology  atau  CCU)  (jika  sudah  diterapkan  pada pabrik Perseroan);
- · Memanfatkan CO  sebagai substitusi asam sulfat untuk 2 menetralkan air limbah;
- · Memanfaatkan  gas nitrogen cair untuk teknologi pengolahan kemiri;
- · Penggantian secara bertahap dari penggunaan bahan bakar solar ke bahan bakar dexlite;
- · Membatasi  penggunaan  listrik  seperti  penerangan jalan umum, yang diatur waktu menyala dan matinya serta  pembatasan  penggunaan  listrik  di office,  yang menyala selama 9 jam pada hari kerja dan mati 24 jam untuk hari libur;
- · Membatasi penggunaan listrik dengan mengatur waktu  penyalaan  dan  pemadaman  di Head  Office dan  penerangan  jalan  umum  yang  hanya  diaktifkan masing-masing selama 9 jam dan mati selama 24 jam di hari libur;
- · Secara bertahap, distribusi dilakukan oleh pihak ketiga sehingga emisi atas distribusi tidak seluruhnya dibebankan kepada Perseroan;

In 2023, the Company  recorded  increased  emissions from  21,436  Ton  CO e  to  24,260  Ton  CO e.  This  increase 2 2 in emissions is due to the Company's production. These emissions  are  not  produced  directly  by  the  Company, but  because  the  Company's  production  activities  use electricity  as  non-renewable  energy  that  still  produces emissions.

## Emission Control Efforts

The  Company's  efforts  in  controlling  emissions  are  as follows:

- · In factories with extensive lands, the Company implements  the  green  factory  concept  to  green  the unbuilt  land  with  plants  to  reduce  air  pollution  and create a more lush and pleasant factory atmosphere;
- · Using separation, capture, and utilization technology (Carbon Capture and Utilization technology or CCU) (if already applied in the Company's factories);
- · Utilizing CO 2 as a substitute for sulfuric acid to neutralize wastewater;
- · Utilizing liquid nitrogen gas for candlenut processing technology;
- · Gradually replacing the use of diesel fuel with dexlite fuel;
- · Limiting  the  use  of  electricity  such  as  public  street lighting, which is set to turn on and off at certain times and limiting the use of electricity in the office, which is on for 9 hours on workdays and off for 24 hours on holidays;
- · Limiting  electricity  use  by  regulating  the  time  of ignition  and  blackout  in  the  Head  Office  and  public street lighting that is only activated for 9 hours each and off for 24 hours on holidays;
- · Gradually, distribution is carried out by third parties so  that  emissions  from  distribution  are  not  entirely charged to the Company;

