Industrial  gas  processing  can  reduce  Greenhouse  Gas (GHG)  emissions  with  carbon  capture  and  utilization technology  (CCU)  through  the  carbon  dioxide  capture process to be recycled or used for other purposes.

In 2022, the Company embarked on an innovative project in collaboration with its Subsidiary, PT Samator  Gas Industri.  This  project  involved  the  application  of  carbon capture and utilization technology (CCU) in the Enhance Oil Recovery (EOR) Project with PT Pertamina EP. The project was conducted at the CO  removal facility of PT Pertamina 2 EP's  Collection  Station  (SP)  in  Subang  and  Cilamaya.  The collected CO  gas from the separation process was absorbed 2 using  an  absorption  system  with  methyl  diethanolamine (MDEA) medium until the CO  content dropped to less than 2 5%. This CO was then processed into economically valuable 2 products for other industries.

Considering the application of this technology is project based, hence in 2023 the Company still in the evaluation phase  for  future  collaborations.  The  Company  always strives to reduce emissions through the emission control initiatives mentioned above.

