When risks are identified as unacceptable, the Implementation Team and management work together to establish risk controls to prevent accidents. Management determines risk control in accordance with the risk control hierarchy, which includes the following steps:

- · Eliminating processes, equipment/machines, raw materials/materials, and dangerous behavior;
- · Substituting processes, equipment/machines, raw materials/materials, and dangerous behavior;
- · Applying  engineering  work  on  hazardous  processes and equipment/machines;
- · Using  administrative  measures  to  control  processes, equipment/machines,  raw  materials/materials,  and hazardous behavior; and
- · Utilizing Personal Protective Equipment (PPE).

After conducting an identification process, the gas factory of the Company has identified that filling carbide into the reactor at the acetylene factory poses a high risk of gas explosion.  To  prevent  such  incidents,  explosion-proof equipment  has  been  installed,  nitrogen  gas  injection  is carried  out  during  filling,  warning  signs  have  been  put up, and workers performing this task are required to wear personal protective equipment.

To reduce the risk of work-related accidents, the Company mandates the use of personal protective equipment such as  glasses,  helmets,  shoes,  and  gloves  for  all  workers, including those  responsible  for product  distribution. Additionally, the Company conducts regular maintenance of  all  its  facilities  and  infrastructure  and  enforces  strict policies  within  the  factory  environment.  These  policies include:

- · Strictly prohibiting smoking within the factory premises.
- · Conducting routine maintenance of factory equipment.
- · Establishing a safe work system for employees and the environment.
- · Developing  a work  program  that ensures Safety, Occupational  Health,  and  the  Environment,  as  well as potential hazards related to the entire production process, are continuously monitored and improved.
- · Maintaining the workplace in a safe condition without any  danger  to  Occupational  Safety,  Health,  and  the Environment.
- · Providing appropriate personal protective equipment related to Occupational Safety, Health, and the Environment to employees and visitors.

- · Menempatkan kebijakan kebersihan lingkungan yang merupakan  bagian  tidak  terpisahkan  dari  kebijakan Keselamatan,  Kesehatan  Kerja  dan  Lingkungan  dan senantiasa  memastikan  kebersihan  lingkungan  yang baik untuk menghindari kecelakaan yang besar (Major Accident); dan
- · Menerapkan sistem reward and punishment berkaitan dengan Keselamatan, Kesehatan Kerja dan Lingkungan, tertulis dalam Peraturan Perseroan.

